Key Risk Areas Identified

⦁	Cloud Misconfigurations: Non-compliant resources (e.g., public storage buckets, overly permissive IAM roles).
⦁	Vulnerability Exploitation: Unpatched container images or third-party libraries detected during scans.
⦁	Data Loss or Exfiltration: Risks due to exposed services or lack of encryption.
⦁	Privilege Escalation: IAM roles/users with excessive permissions, including potential admin path chaining.
⦁	Resource Hijacking: Detection of unauthorized usage (e.g., crypto mining or misuse of compute).
⦁	Operational Disruption: Unplanned changes or shadow IT resources affecting service integrity.
⦁	Lack of Accountability Mapping: Gaps in aligning alert ownership with ITSM teams and business units.
⦁	Internet Exposure: Publicly accessible cloud assets (e.g., EC2, RDS, S3) without proper controls.



